# XOS Session Pipeline (thin gate)

Before coding on a non-trivial task, follow `docs/xos_agent_playbook.md` §6.0. Do not dump full prompt text here.

## Auto-route (Mike describes the task; you pick the stage)

| Mike signal | Stage |
|---|---|
| How does X work / map ground truth | **0 Research** — facts + file:line only; no code; STOP |
| Feature / non-trivial fix / unclear architecture | **1 Diagnostic** — 3 options + files/lines; no code; STOP for `כן`/`yes` |
| Tiny bug / one-line / confirmed Architecture | **2 Execute** — atomic diffs |
| After Stage 2 on automation, webhooks, RLS, Shabbat, guest routing | **3 QA** — §8.3 checklist → P0 or `PASSED QA` |
| `תעלה` / `yes deploy` | **4 Deploy** — checklist layers only |
| `רק research` / `רק diagnostic` / `תריץ QA` | Force that stage |

## Hard stops

- Stage 0 / 1: never write or propose code until Mike confirms.
- Stage 2: atomic diffs; reuse `_shared`/utils; invalidate cache on mutations that feed cached UI.
- Never commit/push/db push/functions deploy without explicit approval.
- Hebrew chat to Mike; English in code/docs/commits.
